<p>Alexander played Boxall in the UK & Ireland touring production of Titanic.</p>
<p>Theatre includes: Dad and Lord Toughman in <i>Eugenius!</i> (The Other Palace); Frid  and Liebesliede in <i>A Little Night Music</i>, <i>Tuxedo Junction</i>, <i>The Devil And The Deep Blue Sea</i>, Greylag and Turkey in <i>Honk!</i> (Watermill Theatre); <i>Carousel</i> (London Coliseum/ENO); Herr Zeller in <i>The Sound Of Music</i>, <i>The Songbook Of Judy Garland</i>, Archibald Craven in <i>The Secret Garden In Concert</i>, <i>Chess</i>, <i>Aspects Of Love</i>, featured vocalist for <i>Spirit Of The Dance</i> (UK tours); Robert Steele and Mr Oscar in <i>Dessa Rose</i> (Trafalgar Studios); <i>Carousel</i> (Barbican Theatre/Opera North); <i>Masterclass</i> (Vaudeville Theatre); Father in <i>Ragtime</i>, Eddie Yeager in <i>Do I Hear A Waltz?</i> (Landor Theatre); Sheldrake in <i>Sunset Boulevard</i> (Harold Pinter Theatre); <i>Hair!</i> (Octagon Theatre, Yeovil); <i>Fanny The Musical</i> (Lost Musicals/Sadler’s Wells); seasons at <i>Thursford Christmas Spectacular</i>.</p>
<p>Alexander was a principal vocalist with the resident company on board the Queen Mary 2 for its maiden and inaugural voyages.
Opera includes: tenor roles in <i>L’Elisir D'Amore</i>, <i>Lucia di Lammermoor</i>, <i>The Merry Widow</i>, <i>The Magic Flute</i>, <i>Don Carlos</i>, <i>The Barber Of Seville (Pavilion Opera); Mozart's <i>Impressario, <i>Cavalleria Rusticana, <i>Don Giovanni, <i>The Marriage Of Figaro</i> (Zeist Festival, Amsterdam); <i>Carmen</i> (O2, Raymond Gubbay); <i>Opera On The Run</i> (UK, Europe & Asia).</p>
<p>Film and television includes: <i>The Sound Of Music Live; The Young Victoria; The Oxford Murders; The Paul O’Grady Show; Popstar To Operastar; Any Dream Will Do.</i></p>

